We had room on 4th floor -- with ear-plugs the noise was not a problem and I would not let it put you off.	We had a room facing away from the street, so there was minimal traffic noise.	It is NOT the best place to sleep, as the walls are quite thin and you could hear chatter from the hallways as well as traffic noise from the street.	We got a room on the 4th floor and it was surprisingly quiet- I live in the city myself so I was prepared for some street noise.	There is no getting away from the fact that traffic noise thru the night is loud, even on the 4th floor.